[1] Cholera - Angola (Namibe)
Date: Fri 14 Mar 2008
Source: Angola Press (ANGOP) [edited]
<http://www.angolapress-angop.ao/noticia-e.asp?ID=602550>


At least 5 people died of cholera, out of the 29 cases recorded in Virei
District, south western Namibe Province, since 9 Feb 2008, ANGOP has
learned. The provincial director of health, Pedro Viyayauka, said other 45
cases were recorded in Namibe District in the same month, totalling 74 in
the whole province.

There is medicine and medical assistance, he said, adding that people are
advised to follow the preventive measures.

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The province of Namibe in the south west corner of the country can be seen
on a map at <http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/angola.pdf>.
- Mod.LL]

